library(tidyverse)
library(CodeClanData)
library(tidyr)
revenue <- qb_revenue_breakdown
sales <- qb_monthly_sales
competitors <- qb_competitors
devices <- qb_device_data

#q1

col_scheme <- c("#E89FE9", "#50434F", "#B6A7B5", "#F9A472", "#BD7040")
revenue %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Year,
         y = Revenue,
         fill = Product))+
  geom_col()+
  labs(title = "Annual Revenue Breakdown by Product",
       y = "Revenue (£)")+
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("Accesories" = "#E89FE9",
                               "Smart Watches" = "#50434F",
                               "Subscription Services" = "#B6A7B5",
                               "Trackers" = "#BD7040"))+
  theme_light()

#q2

kwikbit_sales <- sales %>% 
  filter(Cashflow == "Kwikbit Unit 1 Sales")

kwikbit_sales %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Date,
             y = Amount))+
  geom_line()+
  labs(title = "Kwikbit Monthly Sales",
       y = "Revenue (£)")+
  theme_light()

#q3

cost_rev <- qb_monthly_sales %>% 
  filter(Cashflow != "Kwikbit Unit 1 Sales")

cost_rev %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Date,
             y = Amount,
             colour = Cashflow))+
  geom_line()+
  labs(title = "Monthly Qwikbit Sales",
       y = "Revenue (£)")+
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("Cost" = "#E89FE9",
                               "Total Revenue" = "#50434F"))+
  theme_light()

#q4

competitors %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Year,
             y = Revenue,
             group = Company,
             fill = Company))+
  geom_area()+
  labs(title = "Industry Sales",
       y = "revenue £")+
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("Competitor 1" = "#E89FE9",
                               "Competitor 2" = "#50434F",
                               "Competitor 3" = "#B6A7B5",
                               "Competitor 4" = "#BD7040"))+
  theme_light()

#q5

competitors %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Year,
             y = Revenue,
             group = Company,
             colour = Company))+
  geom_line()+
  geom_point()+
  labs(title = "Competitor Sales Figures",
       y = "Revenue £")+
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("Competitor 1" = "#E89FE9",
                               "Competitor 2" = "#50434F",
                               "Competitor 3" = "#B6A7B5",
                               "Competitor 4" = "#BD7040"))+
  theme_light()

#q6

unique(devices$id)
[1] person2 person5 person1 person3 person4
Levels: person1 person2 person3 person4 person5
unique(devices$device)
[1] qikbit1     competitor1 competitor2 competitor3
Levels: qikbit1 competitor1 competitor2 competitor3
devices <- devices %>% 
  group_by(hours, id, device, ) %>% 
  summarise(counts = sum(counts), .groups = "keep")

devices %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = hours,
             y = counts, 
             group = id,
             colour = device))+
  geom_line()+
  facet_grid(id ~ device)+
  labs(title = "Step tracking vs competitors",
       y = "Step counts")+
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("competitor1" = "#E89FE9",
                               "competitor2" = "#50434F",
                               "competitor3" = "#B6A7B5",
                               "qikbit1" = "#BD7040"))+
  theme_light()
